It appears that our paragraph isn’t processing correctly. The code component handles inline code with text, which is good. However, I need to check how `exposeHtmlComments` converts HTML comments to inline code strings. ReactMarkdown creates a code node for comments, but does the code inside `<pre>` have a `className`? It seems there might not be a class for plain code fences. I should also consider whether `exposeHtmlComments` leaves raw HTML intact. Lastly, I need to consider the status of PlanLists and ensure my snippets reflect only the relevant changes without including PlanLists.
